  "invariants": [
    {
      "id": "B1",
      "rule": "A physical execution identity is the canonical hash of head, command_digest, environment_digest, tool_version, and purpose; when fresh execution is required, fresh_requirement_id is an additional mandatory identity component. target, cycle_id, and unit_id are attribution only and are never identity components."
    },
    {
      "id": "B2",
      "rule": "At most one active claim may exist for a physical execution identity. A succeeded identity returns reusable evidence, an active identity rejects a duplicate claim, and retries may not exceed max_physical_runs without an owner-visible gate."
    },
    {
      "id": "B3",
      "rule": "Evidence reuse requires both matching physical identity and applicable criteria_digest, covered_paths, surface_digest, purpose, independence, and impact_set. Invalidation is explicit and immutable. Development verification, one integration-head full gate, independent review, and finding-scoped delta verification remain mandatory where required."
    },
    {
      "id": "B4",
      "rule": "Required capabilities and preflight checks fail closed before dispatch or external mutation. A capability probe result is cached by mission_id, capability_id, and environment_digest so an unavailable capability is not repeatedly probed by parallel tracks. A paid mutation permit must pin one mutation_request and matching authorization; authorization quota is atomically claimed by authorization_digest, mutation_request_digest, and occurrence_index before mutation, and the consumption and mutation receipts must cross-reference each other."
    },
    {
      "id": "B5",
      "rule": "Agent token budgets and external spend authorizations are separate domains. External mutations with cost require an unexpired owner-approved authorization and matching preflight receipt; null token telemetry is never counted as zero; closeout requires integration, verification, review, delivery, mutation, cleanup, and preserved-user-change receipts applicable to the integration head."
    }
  ],
